  <title class="- topic/title ">Widget Offers</title>
  <shortdesc class="- topic/shortdesc ">Use Widget offers to host your own
	 offer content outside of Target. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
    <p class="- topic/p ">Widget offers are similar to a standard offer hosted
		outside of Target. They allow offer content to that's stored on your server to
		be deployed, allowing for more sophisticated and dynamic usage. Widget offers
		retrieve content from a URL, caching and serving that content for approximately
		two hours. 
	 </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">Widget offers provide some dynamic content generation
		capabilities that other outside offers do not. If the mbox serving the offer
		contains mbox parameters such as 
		<!--<codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">mboxProductID</codeph> and 
		--><codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">mbox.offerId</codeph><!--, the 
		<codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">productId=[PRODUCT_ID]</codeph>-->
		and 
		<codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">offerID=[OFFERID]</codeph> URL
		parameters are appended to the requested URL. These parameters can be used by a
		service available at the Widget offer URL to return outside content that uses
		product or order information from your mboxes. 
	 </p>
    <p class="- topic/p ">The Widget offer is also accessible through the API
		to programatically create offers outside of Target. 
	 </p>
  </conbody>
